6050L-1ND -- 1.66 magnitude seismic event at 6:30 AM (May 17).
The event occurred 13:30 hours after blasting the heading. The bench (8ft) was being performed on the heading. Previous to this event, four
significant magnitude events had happened within standoff(6h)
Seismic procedure was followed, and heading was restricted until seismicity reached background levels at 12 pm.
